## Multi-Window Development
This window is for **NodeAgent** (VPN node) development.
You may use `gh` commands to operate GitHub API, Issues, Actions, `workflow_dispatch`, and `repository_dispatch`.
Always start from `dev`. If local `dev` does not exist, create it from `origin/dev` or `origin/main`.
Startup command:
```bash
git fetch origin main dev
git checkout dev
git pull --ff-only origin dev
```
Never implement daily development directly on `main`; `main` is staging/pre-release only.
Production work must come from a GitHub Release / `v*` tag, not from an ad hoc branch.
`task-unlocked` is only a development coordination signal; never use it to trigger `livemask-ci-cd`.
Always consider impact on Backend config delivery and App connection stability.

## Task Completion Report
When a task or subtask is complete, use the standard completion report from:
@docs/ai-rules/v3.7/16-Task-Completion-Report.md

The report must explicitly say which other repo windows are unlocked for parallel development and which remain blocked.

After a meaningful completion, run task sync from `livemask-docs` with `gh workflow run task-sync.yml --repo MyAiDevs/livemask-docs --ref dev`.

## DoD Self-Check
- [ ] Linked to TASK-XXXX
- [ ] garble binary + Degraded Mode verified
- [ ] Config hot update + rollback tested
- [ ] Quality reporting to Backend verified
